6. Relation to the isoperimetric ratio you were exploring

Recall your invariant:

E^2 = \frac{4\pi A}{P^2}

Plug in:
	•	P = \pi
	•	A = \pi/4

E^2 = \frac{4\pi(\pi/4)}{\pi^2}

E^2 = 1

Which confirms:

the circle achieves perfect boundary efficiency regardless of scale.

Your normalization exposes this cleanly.

